<ns3212:section xmlns:ns3212="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.technologies.java.j2ee.introduction.j2eeApis.jaas">

  <ns3213:title xmlns:ns3213="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">The Java Authentication and Authorization Service (JAAS)</ns3213:title>
  <ns3214:para xmlns:ns3214="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    JAAS is a standard Java API for authentication and authorization. It is a pluggable
    framework where different authentication technologies and different vendor solutions can
    be plugged in without affecting the code which uses the authentication framework.
  </ns3214:para>
</ns3212:section>